parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the differential pinion bearing can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a loud grinding or whining noise
the vehicle vibrates or shakes
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch assembly can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
